Rating: 3
Though it was slightly crumbly around the edges, the cake was moist and fudgy inside. The chocolate (I used Callebaut bittersweet) and plumped tart cherries were a delicious combination, and the cake was a snap to make and stayed moist for a few days. I agree that semisweet chocolate would make too sweet a cake. A springform pan worked fine.

Rating: 4
Very rich and moist. The cherries must be tart to counter the sweetness/richness of the rest of the cake. We used bittersweet chocolate and feel very strongly that using semi-sweet would have been a big mistake. Usually we do not like cherries except for fresh fruit. This was a delightful surprise!

Rating: 4
This cake is easy and quick to bake. Its size and ease of baking make it a good choice for a small dinner or birthday party. It has an excellent and sophisticated flavor and looks pretty on a cake stand with the powdered sugar, or not (I've made it both ways this month). Highly-recommended.